This next .pdf is one that I just found for a solid state subcritical accelerator-boosted energy amplifier.  The reason why I find this interesting is the EXTREMELY rugged design (it's literally a solid block of beryllium with uranium embedded in it) and the high gain in thermal power it demonstrates.  The Promethius project is working to make a 250 kilowatt electric source.  Imagine one of the instruments is a proton accelerator (which could be used to do lots of useful science) and we include one of these EA's as a part of a high thrust rocket design.  From an input beam of 250 kilowatts, I could see one of these making 5 megawatts of power or more.  For a year!  Or two!  Ideal for orbital kick manuevers or doing something like boring a hole into Europa's ocean.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This is a really amazing design, deceptively simple, very elegant.  Who would imagine using a hohlraum for somthing like this?  Very exciting stuff. <br>
